def: To carry through; to succeed in; as, you can't come any trickshere. [Slang] To come it, to succeed in a trick of any sort. [Slang]
A form of albumin found in ascitic and certain serous fluids.It is sometimes regarded as a mixture of albumin and mucin.
Pertaining to a draught, or current of air; as, a draughtly,comfortless room.
One skilled in strategy, or the science of directing greatmilitary movements.

To walk through or over; especially, to travel over for thepurpose of surveying or examining; to inspect by traversing;specifically, to inspect officially the boundaries of, as of a townor parish, by walking over the whole line.
Like a beryl; of a light or bluish green color.
In a jovial manner; merrily; gayly. B. Jonson.
Having the form of a lens; lens-shaped.
Propagation from seed. [R.] Sir M. Hale.
Being, or done, in the open air; being or done outside ofcertain buildings, as poorhouses, hospitals, etc.; as, outdoorexercise; outdoor relief; outdoor patients.
